This paper discusses the development and usage of crypto-currencies and blockchain technologies, which are primarily related to computer security (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the theoretical aspects of these currencies, which could fall under distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the regulatory readiness for dealing with transactions in these currencies, which could fall under game theory (cs.GT).
